parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, compromising the safety of vehicle occupants.
symptoms: No airbag deployment in accidents
injuries sustained by occupants
no warning messages or indicators prior to the accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause injuries, accidents, or distractions while driving, compromising the safety of vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Airbag deployment without impact or warning
injuries sustained by occupants
accidents caused by airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Error codes related to the airbag system can indicate a potential problem that may lead to airbag failure or unintended deployment, compromising the safety of vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Error codes such as B1660
seat driver front up circuit open error code
no warning messages or indicators.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays or unavailability of recall repairs can leave vehicles with potentially hazardous defects on the road, compromising the safety of vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Notification of recall
delay or unavailability of repair parts
no assistance from manufacturer or dealer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to become unsafe to drive, leading to potential accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Grinding sound
sudden loss of power
hesitation when accelerating
failure to downshift
and inability to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the TCS/DSC control can cause the loss of power to the wheels, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Hesitation when accelerating
loss of power to the wheels
and sudden slowing or bogging down of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and flywheel can cause the vehicle to shudder or hesitate, making it difficult to shift gears and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Shuddering or hesitation when shifting gears
particularly from a dead stop
and play in the manual gear lever.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hesitation of the transmission can cause the vehicle to slow down or fail to accelerate, leading to potential accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Hesitation when accelerating
failure to downshift
and sudden slowing or bogging down of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high pressure fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall, especially at high speeds, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving
especially at high speeds (above 70mph)
the vehicle jerks when trying to accelerate
the vehicle is unsafe to drive
and the engine may hesitate or lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The high-pitched noise when pressing the brakes can be a sign of a potential brake system failure, which can lead to reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: High-pitched noise when pressing the brakes
intermittent noise occurrence.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature front rotor wear can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Overheating front rotors
excessive wear on front rotors at low mileage
rotors too hot to touch after short drives.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Forward Collision Warning System and Automatic Emergency Braking
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the forward collision warning system and automatic emergency braking can increase the risk of accidents, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: Failure of forward collision warning system to activate
failure of automatic emergency braking to activate
collision occurs despite system being equipped.
